wnaccord" id="accord_idmg_2"><div class="top-container"><div class="top-g" id="accord_topg_4"><div class="webtop"><span class="idm" id="accord_idm_2">of your own accord</span> </div></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" htag="li" hclass="sense" id="accord_sng_3"><span class="sensetop" hclass="sensetop" htag="span"><span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">without being asked, forced or helped</span></span><ul class="examples" hclass="examples" htag="ul"><li class="" htag="li"><span class="x">He came back of his own accord.</span></li><li class="" htag="li"><span class="x">The symptoms will clear up of their own accord.</span></li></ul>      </li></ol></span> <span class="idm-g" id="accord_idmg_3" sk="withoneaccord" bord="y"><div class="top-container"><div class="top-g" id="accord_topg_5"><div class="webtop"><span class="idm" id="accord_idm_3" cefr="c2">with one accord</span> </div></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" htag="li" hclass="sense" fkcefr="c2" id="accord_sng_4"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="labels" htag="span" hclass="labels">(British English, formal)</span></span> <span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">if people do something <span class="eb">with one accord</span>, they do it at the same time, because they agree with each other</span><span class="topic-g"><span class="prefix">Topics </span><a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/topic/opinion-and-argument?level=c2" title="Topic opinion-and-argument"><span class="topic" href="l2:functions:opinion_and_argument?cefr=c2"><span class="topic_name">Opinion and argument</span><span class="topic_cefr">c2</span></span></a></span>      </li></ol></span></div><span class="dictlink-g"><span class="dictlink">See <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/american_english/accord_1" title=" definition in American English
